net.joala.expression

Class AbstractExpression<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.joala.expression.AbstractExpression<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the result type of the expression
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Expression<T>, org.hamcrest.SelfDescribing
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    UriStatusCodeExpression

    public abstract class AbstractExpression<T>
extends Object
implements Expression<T>

    Convenience abstract implementation of Expression which can get a simple description via constructor. Thus you can skip declaring the method describeTo(Description).

    Since:
    2/27/12
